		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">LDON<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sun, Mar 14th 12:04 AM 2004 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=1079240653306&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=1079240653306&num=1&page=&post=1&replyto=1079240653306"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=1079240653306></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=73658"><span id=Sage>DavivMcD</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>346 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Anyone ever get anything good from the LDON chests/coffins/boxes?<br><br>For me, I either get it disarmed on the first try and find something crappy, or I try forever and never get it open before the dungeon pops or the chest explodes.<br><br>So I'm thinking there are 'easy' and 'hard' boxes, with bad and good loot respectively. Has anyone here ever opened one of the hard ones and gotten something good in it? I hve 197 sense traps and 200 disarm traps skill, so there better be some damn good loot in the hard ones, since I've failed hundreds, maybe thousands, of times and never succeeded once.<br><br>And does anyone know if there are any items with +% to sense or disarm traps? If there are they're most likely 65 req. lvl, but I'm interested anyway. Also, has anyone noticed that sometimes you or a group member gets &quot;You can't loot the corpse with hostile monsters in the area&quot; or similar message when they try to loot an opened box? It looks like a bug to me but I don't know the specifics of when it happens yet.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Dacek Belmont<br>52nd Dwarf Rogue<br>Xegony<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=935771" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=935771</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Mar 15th 8:31 AM 2004 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=1079240653306&num=1&page=&post=1&replyto=1079357419187877129"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=1079357419187877129></a></small>| <span id=fs8>Edited: 2004-03-15 08:43:14</span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=61546"><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>1236 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.69]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>The Safehouse has a good thread on LDoN chests/boxes.&nbsp;&nbsp;But I can share my experience:<br><br>There are 4 kinds of traps on chests/boxes/barrels/urns in LDoN: Mechanical, Magical, Unopenable and Cursed.  Mechanical chests have traps and locks that can be opened only by rogues/bards. The Magical kind require a mage class to open with a special spell that removes the magical wards.  The Cursed kind are just like the magic kind but require a spell from a priest class.  The Unopenable types have no traps or locks.  They cannot be opened unless you attack them and beat them open. <br><br>How do you tell the difference? If its a magic chest then the chest will often move or bounce around on its own.  If its cursed you will see runes and symbols on it when you inspect it with /inspect.  I find that if you detect traps a few times and fail then the box is likely magical or cursed. You can, at that point try picking the lock.  But if that fails after a couple of tries get your casters to disarm it.  Most casters won't spend the adventure pts to buy those spells, btw, so you may be stuck. Mechanical traps and locks should open on the first try (rarely the 2nd) unless your disarm traps and pick locks skill are pretty poor.  My rule of thumb is that if I get a message saying &quot;you are unable to determine if this chest is trapped&quot; I leave it alone until a caster can disarm it.<br><br>Oh, yes you can get anything from junk to nice items in chests. Its completely random.  Once I got a piece of armor slightly better than studded leather.  Once I got a 1 dose invisibility potion.  Another time I got a +5 STA augmentation and another time a black sapphire.<br><br><i><span class=sm>Edited, Mon Mar 15 08:41:48 2004 by Slipskin</span class=sm></i></p><span class=sm>------------